00:00:21.200 --> 00:00:24.380
BARTON ZWIEBACH: Let's begin.

00:00:24.380 --> 00:00:28.730
So today's lecture will
deal with the subject

00:00:28.730 --> 00:00:33.620
of squeeze states
and photon states.

00:00:33.620 --> 00:00:38.240
And it all builds up from
the ideas of coherent states

00:00:38.240 --> 00:00:41.130
that we were talking
about last time.

00:00:41.130 --> 00:00:46.335
So let me begin by reminding
you about the few facts

00:00:46.335 --> 00:00:49.350
that we had about
coherent states.

00:00:49.350 --> 00:00:53.290
So a coherent state was
born by taking the ground

00:00:53.290 --> 00:00:56.870
state of the harmonic
oscillator and displacing it

00:00:56.870 --> 00:01:01.400
with a translation
operator some distance, x0.

00:01:01.400 --> 00:01:03.700
And then we let
it go, and we saw

00:01:03.700 --> 00:01:09.270
that this sort of wave function
would just move from the left

00:01:09.270 --> 00:01:13.480
and to the right coherently,
without spreading out,

00:01:13.480 --> 00:01:15.180
without changing shape.

00:01:15.180 --> 00:01:17.740
It would move in a nice way.

00:01:17.740 --> 00:01:23.050
Now, this was obtained with
a translation operator, which

00:01:23.050 --> 00:01:27.980
was an exponential that had
on the exponent the momentum

00:01:27.980 --> 00:01:29.900
operator.

00:01:29.900 --> 00:01:34.780
But we realized eventually that
the reason it all works out

00:01:34.780 --> 00:01:39.440
is because its exponential
of something that

00:01:39.440 --> 00:01:43.600
depends on creation or
annihilation operators,

00:01:43.600 --> 00:01:46.130
and we could do
something more general,

00:01:46.130 --> 00:01:50.880
which was to use a
complex number, alpha,

00:01:50.880 --> 00:01:54.430
and define a
displacement operator,

00:01:54.430 --> 00:02:00.110
a more general one, that is
some linear combination of a

00:02:00.110 --> 00:02:05.370
and a dagger with alpha and
the complex conjugate of alpha.

00:02:05.370 --> 00:02:12.230
So this is only proportional to
the momentum if alpha is real,

00:02:12.230 --> 00:02:15.900
but if alpha is not real,
that operator in the exponent

00:02:15.900 --> 00:02:17.700
is not quite the momentum.

00:02:17.700 --> 00:02:22.090
It's something that has a
bit of position as well.

00:02:22.090 --> 00:02:25.420
So this is a more
general operator,

00:02:25.420 --> 00:02:27.690
but on the other
hand, it's clear

00:02:27.690 --> 00:02:30.530
that it's anti-Hermitian,
because if you

00:02:30.530 --> 00:02:34.590
take the dagger of this
thing, this term becomes

00:02:34.590 --> 00:02:38.050
that and that term
becomes this one,

00:02:38.050 --> 00:02:40.270
each one with a change of sign.

00:02:40.270 --> 00:02:44.150
So you're really with an
anti-Hermitian operator.

00:02:44.150 --> 00:02:49.460
Therefore, the whole
operator is unitary

00:02:49.460 --> 00:02:53.960
and you're acting with a
unitary operator on the vacuum.

00:02:53.960 --> 00:02:56.930
And therefore, this state
is also well normalized

00:02:56.930 --> 00:03:00.570
and represents a state
with some expectation

00:03:00.570 --> 00:03:01.980
value of the position.

00:03:01.980 --> 00:03:04.850
Just like a coherent state,
we moved it to the right

00:03:04.850 --> 00:03:08.100
and it had some expectation
value of the position.

00:03:08.100 --> 00:03:11.720
But this one also has
some expectation value

00:03:11.720 --> 00:03:13.450
of the momentum.

00:03:13.450 --> 00:03:21.930
So in fact, we realize that the
real part of alpha in this axis

00:03:21.930 --> 00:03:26.170
was related to the expectation
value of the position divided

00:03:26.170 --> 00:03:27.580
by to the 0.

00:03:27.580 --> 00:03:29.250
So if you produce
a coherent state

00:03:29.250 --> 00:03:35.270
with this value of alpha
in the complex alpha plane,

00:03:35.270 --> 00:03:38.030
well, you go down and
that's the expectation value

00:03:38.030 --> 00:03:39.220
of the position.

00:03:39.220 --> 00:03:42.420
You go horizontally,
well, that's

00:03:42.420 --> 00:03:45.170
the expectation value
of the momentum scaled

00:03:45.170 --> 00:03:49.110
because this alpha is a
pure number, has no units.

00:03:49.110 --> 00:03:55.560
So this x over square root
of 2 d0 and p d0 over h

00:03:55.560 --> 00:04:01.210
bar have no units, and
that's how it should be.

00:04:01.210 --> 00:04:06.520
So we learned also that the
annihilation operator acting

00:04:06.520 --> 00:04:10.560
on this coherent state was
alpha times the coherent state.

00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:13.030
So it's a very simple property.

00:04:13.030 --> 00:04:17.160
That number, alpha,
is the eigenvalue

00:04:17.160 --> 00:04:19.020
of the destruction operator.

00:04:22.250 --> 00:04:26.550
Now, that's a one line
computation based on this,

00:04:26.550 --> 00:04:29.820
or a two line computation maybe.

00:04:29.820 --> 00:04:34.360
But it should be a computation
that is easy for you to do.

00:04:34.360 --> 00:04:40.100
So make sure you
know how to get this

00:04:40.100 --> 00:04:43.750
very quickly from
this definition.

00:04:43.750 --> 00:04:45.570
So that's a coherent state.

00:04:45.570 --> 00:04:48.340
And then the thing we
finished the lecture

00:04:48.340 --> 00:04:53.080
with was with the time evolution
of this coherent state.

00:04:53.080 --> 00:05:00.360
And the time evolution was that
as the state, alpha, in time

00:05:00.360 --> 00:05:06.620
becomes the state alpha at time
t, it remains a coherent state

00:05:06.620 --> 00:05:09.720
but the value of
alpha is changed.

00:05:09.720 --> 00:05:12.160
In fact, the value
of alpha is changed

00:05:12.160 --> 00:05:16.890
in such a way that you can just
imagine this thing rotating,

00:05:16.890 --> 00:05:20.370
and rotating with
angular velocity, omega.

00:05:20.370 --> 00:05:25.870
So this thing was
the coherent state,

00:05:25.870 --> 00:05:30.130
e to the minus i omega t alpha.

00:05:30.130 --> 00:05:34.050
So this whole complex number,
instead of being alpha,

00:05:34.050 --> 00:05:35.030
is just this.

00:05:35.030 --> 00:05:37.650
There's no comma t.

00:05:37.650 --> 00:05:39.880
This is the time
development of the state.

00:05:39.880 --> 00:05:46.330
And there was a phase here, e
to the minus i omega t over 2,

00:05:46.330 --> 00:05:49.540
that was not very relevant.

00:05:49.540 --> 00:05:51.830
But that's what the
state was doing in time.

00:05:51.830 --> 00:05:56.890
So basically, that's
where we got last time.

00:05:56.890 --> 00:06:00.686
Before I push on, do
you have any questions?

00:06:05.710 --> 00:06:11.760
I did post the notes associated
to coherent states about half

00:06:11.760 --> 00:06:15.760
an hour ago, so you have them.

00:06:15.760 --> 00:06:19.830
You do have two problems
on coherent states

00:06:19.830 --> 00:06:24.300
in this homework, so the
notes should help you.

00:06:24.300 --> 00:06:27.260
But any questions
about this picture?

00:06:35.190 --> 00:06:35.690
OK.

00:06:35.690 --> 00:06:38.710
So I want to develop
it a little more

00:06:38.710 --> 00:06:45.730
before starting
with squeeze states.

00:06:45.730 --> 00:06:49.810
So here's what I
want to tell you.

00:06:49.810 --> 00:06:54.516
And this is an intuition that
people have about these states.

00:06:57.500 --> 00:06:59.620
Alpha is a complex number.

00:06:59.620 --> 00:07:02.970
And you know, it's a
well-defined complex number.

00:07:02.970 --> 00:07:06.400
But you know, this
is a coherent state,

00:07:06.400 --> 00:07:11.730
so it's not a
position eigenstate.

00:07:11.730 --> 00:07:14.755
It's not a momentum eigenstate.

00:07:14.755 --> 00:07:17.130
It's not an energy eigenstate.

00:07:17.130 --> 00:07:19.670
It has all kinds
of uncertainties.

00:07:19.670 --> 00:07:24.000
It has uncertainties in
position, in momentum,

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:24.890
and in energy.

00:07:24.890 --> 00:07:26.226
Yes?

00:07:26.226 --> 00:07:30.242
AUDIENCE: On that complex plane
where you have the x and the p,

00:07:30.242 --> 00:07:33.865
are those expectation values
of the position of momentum?

00:07:33.865 --> 00:07:34.740
BARTON ZWIEBACH: Yes.

00:07:34.740 --> 00:07:37.220
I think I wrote them
with expectation values

00:07:37.220 --> 00:07:39.600
of the position of
momentum last time.

00:07:39.600 --> 00:07:40.710
Yes.

00:07:40.710 --> 00:07:43.400
So given alpha,
that number you get

00:07:43.400 --> 00:07:46.740
is the expectation value
of position or expectation

00:07:46.740 --> 00:07:48.336
value of momentum.

00:07:48.336 --> 00:07:48.835
Correct.

00:07:51.930 --> 00:07:56.940
So actually, this is
the expectation value

00:07:56.940 --> 00:07:59.810
of the position,
but the position

00:07:59.810 --> 00:08:03.726
is a little bit rounded.

00:08:03.726 --> 00:08:06.700
Yeah, this is the expectation
value of the position.

00:08:06.700 --> 00:08:07.460
It's a number.

00:08:07.460 --> 00:08:11.360
But intuitively, this
is spread out a little.

00:08:11.360 --> 00:08:16.020
The position is
not just one point.

00:08:16.020 --> 00:08:18.425
This is a coherent state.

00:08:18.425 --> 00:08:21.370
It looks like a
Gaussian wave function.

00:08:21.370 --> 00:08:25.650
The momentum is also
spread out a little.

00:08:25.650 --> 00:08:29.900
So in some sense, many people
draw this as a little blob.

00:08:38.419 --> 00:08:43.039
And that blob represents
your intuition

00:08:43.039 --> 00:08:46.275
that yes, the
expectation value is this

00:08:46.275 --> 00:08:48.210
and the expectation
value is this,

00:08:48.210 --> 00:08:53.680
but the position is, well,
somewhere around this thing

00:08:53.680 --> 00:08:57.890
and somewhere around that stuff.

00:08:57.890 --> 00:09:02.810
You can complain, this is very
hand wavy, but it's useful.

00:09:02.810 --> 00:09:06.660
It's good to have that physical
picture that the state really

00:09:06.660 --> 00:09:11.610
is some sort of blob here, not
that the expectation values are

00:09:11.610 --> 00:09:16.950
not well defined, but rather
that it's something like this.

00:09:16.950 --> 00:09:24.270
And I want to relate it to
an idea that comes along

00:09:24.270 --> 00:09:27.890
with waves, and it's
important for what

00:09:27.890 --> 00:09:30.890
we're going to be
doing later today.

00:09:30.890 --> 00:09:41.920
If you have a wave with energy
e, and suppose your wave

00:09:41.920 --> 00:09:45.740
is a light wave.

00:09:45.740 --> 00:09:49.090
Light wave with energy e.

00:09:49.090 --> 00:09:53.660
And it's described by,
say, A cosine omega t.

00:09:53.660 --> 00:09:56.450
That's some component
of the electric field

00:09:56.450 --> 00:10:00.910
or the magnetic
field for this wave.

00:10:00.910 --> 00:10:01.970
It is like that.

00:10:01.970 --> 00:10:06.190
Well, we've been talking
about energy time uncertainty,

00:10:06.190 --> 00:10:11.580
and we know that unless we
make things very precise.

00:10:11.580 --> 00:10:14.900
It's easy to get things wrong.

00:10:14.900 --> 00:10:20.630
So I will first do
something fairly imprecise

00:10:20.630 --> 00:10:24.550
to give you a feeling of
what people talk about,

00:10:24.550 --> 00:10:27.925
and then we'll use this picture
to do it more precisely.

00:10:30.650 --> 00:10:39.620
So if you have
this wave, the face

00:10:39.620 --> 00:10:44.526
of this wave-- we'll
call it phi-- is omega t.

00:10:44.526 --> 00:10:49.350
And if we are naive
there, the face

00:10:49.350 --> 00:10:54.280
is divided by omega
is the error in time.

00:10:58.090 --> 00:11:05.650
Now, this wave has energy E.
It has some number of photons.

00:11:05.650 --> 00:11:12.245
So the energy, E, is the number
of photons times h bar omega.

00:11:12.245 --> 00:11:14.380
N is equal to number of photons.

00:11:19.900 --> 00:11:29.430
And again, we could say delta
E is delta N h bar omega,

00:11:29.430 --> 00:11:36.270
and then substitute these
two relations into this

00:11:36.270 --> 00:11:37.590
to see what we get.

00:11:37.590 --> 00:11:47.540
Well, delta E is
delta N h bar omega.

00:11:47.540 --> 00:11:51.970
Delta t is delta phi over omega.

00:11:51.970 --> 00:11:55.660
This should be h bar over 2.

00:11:55.660 --> 00:11:59.180
The omegas cancel,
the h bar cancels,

00:11:59.180 --> 00:12:10.860
and you get delta N delta phi
is about 1, or 1 over 2 or 1

00:12:10.860 --> 00:12:12.170
over square root of 2.

00:12:14.680 --> 00:12:17.000
And that's, in
fact, the relation

00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:20.340
that people do take
somewhat seriously,

00:12:20.340 --> 00:12:24.820
if you have a wave
in quantum optics

00:12:24.820 --> 00:12:27.380
and say, well, the uncertainty
in the number of photons

00:12:27.380 --> 00:12:31.590
and the uncertainty in the
coherence of these photons,

00:12:31.590 --> 00:12:36.610
the phases, if they're out of
phase, they're not coherent,

00:12:36.610 --> 00:12:38.360
there's a relation of this kind.

00:12:38.360 --> 00:12:46.410
And this derivation is
certainly pretty bad.

00:12:46.410 --> 00:12:51.470
It's just not
precise because even

00:12:51.470 --> 00:12:55.210
we started with this that is
not precise unless you really

00:12:55.210 --> 00:12:58.590
explain what you
mean by delta t.

00:12:58.590 --> 00:13:02.605
So let's see if we can make
some sense of this picture here.

00:13:05.540 --> 00:13:06.880
So here we go.

00:13:06.880 --> 00:13:10.345
I want to do a small
calculation first.

00:13:15.190 --> 00:13:19.000
So let's see what we have.

00:13:19.000 --> 00:13:23.600
In this coherent state, what
is the expectation value

00:13:23.600 --> 00:13:26.860
of the number operator?

00:13:26.860 --> 00:13:31.720
Expectation value of the
number operator in alpha.

00:13:31.720 --> 00:13:34.210
Well, the number
operator in alpha,

00:13:34.210 --> 00:13:40.000
you would do this a
dagger a in alpha.

00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:47.420
These are easy to do because a
on alpha is alpha times alpha,

00:13:47.420 --> 00:13:51.160
and if you dagger that
equation, a dagger on alpha

00:13:51.160 --> 00:13:53.090
is alpha star.

00:13:53.090 --> 00:13:59.720
So you get-- I'll go slowly--
alpha alpha star here,

00:13:59.720 --> 00:14:02.055
and then you get alpha alpha.

00:14:04.990 --> 00:14:07.200
And alpha has unit norm.

00:14:07.200 --> 00:14:12.350
These are numbers, so
this is equal to length

00:14:12.350 --> 00:14:13.605
of alpha squared.

00:14:20.580 --> 00:14:23.990
So if this is a
harmonic oscillator,

00:14:23.990 --> 00:14:28.450
the expectation value of the
number operator, in fact,

00:14:28.450 --> 00:14:33.030
is the length squared
of this vector.

00:14:33.030 --> 00:14:35.480
Now, how about N squared?

00:14:39.030 --> 00:14:41.430
N squared is a little
more work because you

00:14:41.430 --> 00:14:47.410
have alpha a dagger
a a dagger a alpha.

00:14:51.090 --> 00:14:53.885
This one gives me
the factor you know,

00:14:53.885 --> 00:14:56.182
this one gives me
the factor you know.

00:14:56.182 --> 00:15:04.170
And therefore, we already
have alpha squared times alpha

00:15:04.170 --> 00:15:07.950
a a dagger alpha.

00:15:07.950 --> 00:15:10.760
And here, the a's
and the a daggers

00:15:10.760 --> 00:15:14.560
are kind of in the
wrong order because I

00:15:14.560 --> 00:15:21.110
know what a is on a ket,
but a is now on the bra.

00:15:21.110 --> 00:15:23.840
And I know what a
dagger is on the bra,

00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:27.490
but now a dagger is on the ket.

00:15:27.490 --> 00:15:29.130
But the answer is simple.

00:15:29.130 --> 00:15:34.020
You replace this
by the commutator

00:15:34.020 --> 00:15:37.790
plus the reverse order.

00:15:37.790 --> 00:15:41.580
So this is equal to the
commutator, which is 1,

00:15:41.580 --> 00:15:44.425
plus the thing in
the reverse order.

00:15:49.830 --> 00:15:53.380
And this is 1 plus
alpha squared.

00:15:53.380 --> 00:16:00.610
So you have alpha squared
times 1 plus alpha squared,

00:16:00.610 --> 00:16:03.860
and that's the expectation
value of N squared.

00:16:03.860 --> 00:16:07.130
All that, because we're
actually interested in what

00:16:07.130 --> 00:16:13.250
is delta N, the uncertainty
in N in the coherent state.

00:16:13.250 --> 00:16:17.060
And that would be
this, square root

00:16:17.060 --> 00:16:21.750
of this, which is alpha
to the fourth plus alpha

00:16:21.750 --> 00:16:28.550
squared minus the square of
the expectation value, which

00:16:28.550 --> 00:16:33.100
is minus alpha to the fourth.

00:16:33.100 --> 00:16:38.610
And this is length of alpha.

00:16:38.610 --> 00:16:47.876
So the uncertainty in N
is just length of alpha.

00:16:47.876 --> 00:16:55.710
It happens to be the square root
of the expectation value of N.

00:16:55.710 --> 00:16:59.840
So in fact, if you
think of this picture,

00:16:59.840 --> 00:17:03.240
you're tempted to say,
oh, this represents

00:17:03.240 --> 00:17:08.750
the number of excited
states that you have.

00:17:08.750 --> 00:17:14.050
This length represents the
expectation value of N. No.

00:17:14.050 --> 00:17:19.329
The expectation value of
N is this length squared.

00:17:19.329 --> 00:17:27.210
This length represents
delta N in the picture.

00:17:31.930 --> 00:17:36.430
So what else can we say?

00:17:36.430 --> 00:17:40.610
Well, this picture is
useful because now, I

00:17:40.610 --> 00:17:42.905
can be a little
more precise here.

00:17:46.760 --> 00:17:49.390
This thing is rotating.

00:17:49.390 --> 00:17:54.660
That is time evolution
of your coherent state.

00:17:54.660 --> 00:17:57.250
Now, this thing
this rotating, but I

00:17:57.250 --> 00:18:00.040
can ask now how wide this is.

00:18:02.720 --> 00:18:08.400
So what is the uncertainty
in x in a coherent state?

00:18:08.400 --> 00:18:11.190
Well, the uncertainty
in x in a coherent state

00:18:11.190 --> 00:18:14.650
is the same as the uncertainty
of the ground state

00:18:14.650 --> 00:18:17.710
because you just moved it.

00:18:17.710 --> 00:18:19.940
Uncertainty doesn't change.

00:18:19.940 --> 00:18:28.080
So the uncertainty,
delta x, is in fact

00:18:28.080 --> 00:18:36.460
this quantity that we call
d0 over square root of 2.

00:18:36.460 --> 00:18:42.370
That's the uncertainty delta
x, and the uncertainty delta p

00:18:42.370 --> 00:18:49.640
is h bar over d0
square root of 2.

00:18:49.640 --> 00:18:52.670
These are not hard to remember.

00:18:52.670 --> 00:18:57.990
d0 is the length scale of
the harmonic oscillator,

00:18:57.990 --> 00:19:01.080
so that's typically what
the uncertainty should be.

00:19:01.080 --> 00:19:04.620
The square root of 2, yes,
it's hard to remember.

00:19:04.620 --> 00:19:07.000
But delta p is this one.

00:19:07.000 --> 00:19:08.540
And then the other
thing that you

00:19:08.540 --> 00:19:12.100
know is that the product
should be h bar over 2,

00:19:12.100 --> 00:19:14.030
so that is correct.

00:19:16.640 --> 00:19:18.970
Now, look at this.

00:19:18.970 --> 00:19:21.715
How big is this thing?

00:19:21.715 --> 00:19:26.980
If the uncertainty in x is
d0 over square root of 2,

00:19:26.980 --> 00:19:36.540
this width is about
how much, roughly?

00:19:47.985 --> 00:19:48.485
Nobody?

00:19:51.170 --> 00:20:00.230
This is the uncertainty in
x, d0 over square root of 2

