Well, it goes a little singular,
but not terribly singular.

01:18:23.960 --> 01:18:27.170
Gamma is going to
infinity, so cosh

01:18:27.170 --> 01:18:30.150
is going to infinity as well.

01:18:30.150 --> 01:18:36.230
So the state is going kind
of to 0, but 0 sub infinity.

01:18:36.230 --> 01:18:39.690
It's proportional, but
the exponential is good.

01:18:39.690 --> 01:18:45.480
Exponential of minus
1/2 tangent of gamma

01:18:45.480 --> 01:18:49.850
as gamma goes to
infinity is just 1.

01:18:49.850 --> 01:18:58.540
And this is a dagger a
dagger on the vacuum.

01:18:58.540 --> 01:19:04.135
This state is in almost
terrible danger to be infinite.

01:19:04.135 --> 01:19:07.260
If you try to find
its wave function,

01:19:07.260 --> 01:19:09.560
you're not going to be
able to normalize it.

01:19:09.560 --> 01:19:11.890
You've reached the
end of the road

01:19:11.890 --> 01:19:15.340
kind of thing because of this.

01:19:15.340 --> 01:19:16.900
Gamma goes to infinity.

01:19:16.900 --> 01:19:19.440
This is going to
be infinite here

01:19:19.440 --> 01:19:21.270
because this state,
if you compute

01:19:21.270 --> 01:19:24.650
its overlap with
itself, is blowing up.

01:19:24.650 --> 01:19:26.670
And here, you see
the niceness of this.

01:19:26.670 --> 01:19:30.000
It also suggests that gamma
can go from plus infinity

01:19:30.000 --> 01:19:33.310
to minus infinity, and
that's a natural thing.

01:19:33.310 --> 01:19:37.630
Nevertheless, here, it goes
from plus 1 to minus 1.

01:19:37.630 --> 01:19:40.900
If you had a number 3
here, this is a state

01:19:40.900 --> 01:19:43.600
that blows much worse
than the worst delta

01:19:43.600 --> 01:19:47.570
function or derivative or
square that you've ever had.

01:19:47.570 --> 01:19:51.290
It's just unbelievably
divergent because it just

01:19:51.290 --> 01:19:53.160
can't exist, this state.

01:19:53.160 --> 01:19:58.100
You're going beyond infinity
here to go behind this thing.

01:19:58.100 --> 01:20:00.430
So it's just pretty
much impossible.

01:20:00.430 --> 01:20:03.250
So the limit is
states are reasonable

01:20:03.250 --> 01:20:07.400
as long as this quadratic
form goes from minus 1 to 1.

01:20:07.400 --> 01:20:11.660
And when you go to 1, you get
this, and what should this be?

01:20:11.660 --> 01:20:14.940
This should be the
wave function I

01:20:14.940 --> 01:20:17.240
associated to a delta function.

01:20:17.240 --> 01:20:24.490
This would be the position
state, x equals 0.

01:20:24.490 --> 01:20:27.250
Roughly, it's a delta function.

01:20:27.250 --> 01:20:31.040
And indeed, if you
act with x on it,

01:20:31.040 --> 01:20:33.620
x, remember, is a plus a dagger.

01:20:37.640 --> 01:20:38.750
Act on this exponential.

01:20:42.330 --> 01:20:45.180
Now, do you remember
how to do that?

01:20:45.180 --> 01:20:50.330
This a dagger doesn't do
anything but the a goes here,

01:20:50.330 --> 01:20:52.060
and it's a trivial commutator.

01:20:52.060 --> 01:20:55.400
You get minus a dagger.

01:20:55.400 --> 01:20:58.800
So it actually kills
this and gives you 0.

01:20:58.800 --> 01:21:03.455
So in fact, the exposition
operator acting on here

01:21:03.455 --> 01:21:06.690
gives you 0.

01:21:06.690 --> 01:21:11.590
It looks like it is really
the state x equals 0.

01:21:11.590 --> 01:21:17.210
If you go the other way
around, and you take gamma

01:21:17.210 --> 01:21:23.380
to be minus infinity, the
only thing that changes here

01:21:23.380 --> 01:21:24.110
is the sign.

01:21:24.110 --> 01:21:32.430
So this is like the delta of
x, or the x equals 0 state.

01:21:32.430 --> 01:21:40.410
And if you take 0 minus
infinity, goes like x minus 1/2

01:21:40.410 --> 01:21:47.510
plus 1/2 a dagger a
dagger on the vacuum.

01:21:47.510 --> 01:21:51.430
And this state is a delta
function in momentum.

01:21:51.430 --> 01:21:55.950
It's the momentum
state p equals 0.

01:21:55.950 --> 01:21:57.210
Why?

01:21:57.210 --> 01:22:01.560
Because gamma is going
to minus infinity.

01:22:01.560 --> 01:22:05.380
The uncertainty of
momentum is going to 0.

01:22:05.380 --> 01:22:09.220
And therefore, indeed, if
you act with the momentum

01:22:09.220 --> 01:22:11.570
operator on this
state, it's like acting

01:22:11.570 --> 01:22:15.130
with a minus a
dagger, and you've

01:22:15.130 --> 01:22:18.160
changed the sign of this, but
you've changed the sign here,

01:22:18.160 --> 01:22:20.950
so it also kills this state.

01:22:20.950 --> 01:22:26.240
So it looks like we can really
construct position and momentum

01:22:26.240 --> 01:22:29.000
eigenstates now with
squeezed states,

01:22:29.000 --> 01:22:31.200
and that's what they
are supposed to be.

01:22:31.200 --> 01:22:34.690
A squeezed state is something
that has been squeezed enough

01:22:34.690 --> 01:22:37.060
that you can get
a delta function.

01:22:37.060 --> 01:22:39.490
So how do you finish
that construction?

01:22:39.490 --> 01:22:40.240
Here is the claim.

01:22:43.860 --> 01:22:53.390
Square root of 2 m omega over
h bar x a dagger minus 1/2

01:22:53.390 --> 01:22:59.240
a dagger a dagger
acting on the vacuum.

01:22:59.240 --> 01:23:03.770
This is the claim, that this
is the x position state.

01:23:03.770 --> 01:23:08.150
So basically, you have
to squeeze first and then

01:23:08.150 --> 01:23:13.420
translate this thing
to the exposition.

01:23:13.420 --> 01:23:16.180
So how do you check this?

01:23:16.180 --> 01:23:19.320
Well, you should check
that the x operator, which

01:23:19.320 --> 01:23:27.440
is something times a plus a
dagger acting on this thing

01:23:27.440 --> 01:23:29.420
gives you little x.

01:23:29.420 --> 01:23:32.670
So you should have that
x operator on this thing

01:23:32.670 --> 01:23:35.910
gives you x x.

01:23:35.910 --> 01:23:39.720
And that is going to work out
because the a dagger is going

01:23:39.720 --> 01:23:42.616
to sit here and it's going
to get canceled with the a

01:23:42.616 --> 01:23:46.700
with this, but the
a with this part

01:23:46.700 --> 01:23:49.810
is just going to bring down
an x with the right factor.

01:23:49.810 --> 01:23:54.180
So this state, which is a
squeezed state and a little bit

01:23:54.180 --> 01:24:00.110
of a coherent state as well,
is producing the position

01:24:00.110 --> 01:24:01.830
eigenstate.

01:24:01.830 --> 01:24:04.100
In the harmonic
oscillator, you can really

01:24:04.100 --> 01:24:05.900
construct the
position eigenstate

01:24:05.900 --> 01:24:08.900
and you can calculate
the normalization.

01:24:08.900 --> 01:24:13.290
The normalization comes out
to be a rather simple thing.

01:24:13.290 --> 01:24:17.190
So at the end of the day,
the position eigenstate

01:24:17.190 --> 01:24:27.720
is m omega over pi h bar to the
1/4 e to the minus m omega x

01:24:27.720 --> 01:24:30.580
squared over 2h bar.

01:24:30.580 --> 01:24:33.570
And this whole
exponential, square root

01:24:33.570 --> 01:24:41.150
of 2 m omega over h bar,
x a dagger minus 1/2

01:24:41.150 --> 01:24:45.050
a dagger a dagger
acting on the vacuum.

01:24:50.850 --> 01:24:55.610
So your basis of creation
and annihilation operators

01:24:55.610 --> 01:24:58.930
on the harmonic oscillator
is flexible enough

01:24:58.930 --> 01:25:02.320
to allow for a concrete
description of your position

01:25:02.320 --> 01:25:06.470
eigenstates, and a
tractable one as well.

01:25:06.470 --> 01:25:16.320
And that's the extreme
limit of squeezing, together

01:25:16.320 --> 01:25:21.090
with some little bit of
coherent displacement.

01:25:21.090 --> 01:25:23.210
Next time, we'll do
our photon states

01:25:23.210 --> 01:25:25.790
and we'll illustrate the
ideas of both coherent

01:25:25.790 --> 01:25:28.620
and squeezed states
at the same time.

